    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: FABCO SDA-12 - DIFFERENTIAL CARRIER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DIFFERENTIAL CARRIER</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>REMOVE FROM AXLE</title>
            <para>All service of the differential carrier assembly requires removal of the assembly from the axle
                housing.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the drain plugs and drain lubricant from axle housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect propeller shaft at pinion yoke.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove both inner axle shafts. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s02010_14.xml" xrefid="hl0201014">INNER AXLE SHAFT REMOVAL</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach differential carrier to a suitable roller jack (refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0201044">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0201044" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201044.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 44. Attachment of Differential Carrier to Roller Jack</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove capscrews and nuts holding differential carrier to axle housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Roll differential carrier away from the axle (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0201045">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0201045" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201045.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 45. Rolling Differential Carrier Away From Axle</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
